                    <img border="0" src="//ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&MarketPlace=US&ASIN=0060684127&ServiceVersion=20070822&ID=AsinImage&WS=1&Format=_SL160_&tag=pastorandrews-20" >
                </a>
                <img src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=pastorandrews-20&l=am2&o=1&a=0060684127" width="1" height="1" border="0" alt="" style="border:none !important; margin:0px !important;" />
                <pTitle>
                    <a target="_blank" href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0060684127/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0060684127&linkCode=as2&tag=pastorandrews-20&linkId=b126ab7fa20013cd852edfabb3a13129">
                        <i>Knowledge of the Holy</i>, by A.W. Tozer
                    </a>
                </pTitle>
                <br />
                <span class="more">
                    I have said before that if there was only one book besides the Bible that I could take with me to a deserted island, it would
                    be <i>Knowledge of the Holy</i>. It is as inspiring as it is informative. Considered by many to be one of the great
                    Christian classics, Knowledge of the Holy eloquently sets forth the majesty of God in his most glorious attributes. If you’re
                    like me, you will come to treasure this work and will return to it, again and again, to feed your soul.
                </span>
            </p>
